data.title: Complete List of NES Video Games from the 80s
data.meta_description: Complete List of NES Video Games from the 80s - Dedicated to everything we Love - Triplets, 80s Music, TV and Culture, Play Classic Arcade Games, Disney
data.text: The Nintendo Entertainment System (also abbreviated as NES or simply called Nintendo) is an 8-bit video game console that was released by Nintendo in North America during 1985 and featured 18 launch titles: 10-Yard Fight, Baseball, Clu Clu Land, Donkey Kong Jr. Math, Duck Hunt, Excitebike, Golf, Gyromite, Hoganâ€™s Alley, Ice Climber, Kung Fu, Mach Rider, Pinball, Stack-Up, Super Mario Bros., Tennis, Wild Gunman, and Wrecking Crew. The NES was succeeded by the Super Nintendo Entertainment System, released in 1991. There are 800 titles in the NES library.
